                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111N83/67</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Norway</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SHFA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Christiania</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-24T15:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 24, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11.34 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1054. Instructions have been received by the British Minister to defer giving the
                    Norwegian Government the time limit warning referred to in my telegram No. 1040
                    of August 21, 3 p.m., regarding mining Norwegian territorial waters. British
                    Minister further informs me that the French Government had given the British
                    Ambassador at Paris to understand that France also desires not to assume a
                    threatening attitude in this matter for the present. I am inclined to think,
                    however, from subsequent conversation with the French Minister, that he had
                    given [intimation] of the warning to the Minister for Foreign Affairs before he
                    learned of his Government’s present attitude.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SHFA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Schoenfeld</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
